column4: I'm making a script and need to match *Chrome*NAME_OF_FLASH_LIB*
with regexp, but I don't have an Ubuntu machine available
I need the output when Chrome is running with a flash been shown
you can try youtube or justin.tv
be sure not to have html5 vids on if on youtube
JmanGuy  did the pastebin do it for you?
you only posted one don't you? The one I saw from you didn't mention any flash plugin, were you watching any flash vid when running ps?
still no flash plugin, maybe you have html5 vids on youtube if that's what you visited? Or maybe chrome on some cases doesn't show an argument with the flash plugin in use.
would you mind going to justin.tv , see any channel, and post "ps aux | grep flash"?
it's set how you requested, and that was the output.
thank you, same output as before but I needed this time, as said, "ps aux | grep flash". But I won't bother you anymore you have done too much thanks :)
thanks again. Seems Chrome don't shows flash plugin in your case. I will have to consider that on my script.
